{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "1c8cf438-bd48-45df-95d0-949dd2931beb",
    "name": "ANF Migrate",
    "description": "This collection automates the migration of NFS/SMB volumes from an on-premises ONTAP cluster to Azure NetApp Files (ANF) using the ANF External Replication (Migration as a Service) feature.\n\nWork through the folders in order:\n\n1. **Azure Authentication** — Obtain an OAuth 2.0 bearer token from Azure AD. This token is stored as a global variable and used by all subsequent API calls.\n2. **Replication Setup** — Create the ANF target volume, establish cluster and SVM peering with the source ONTAP system, and authorize the external replication relationship.\n3. **Pre-Cutover and Cutover** — Monitor and manage the ongoing replication, trigger a final sync, break the replication relationship, and finalize the migration so the ANF volume is ready to serve production workloads.\n\n**Prerequisites**\n- An Azure service principal with Contributor rights on the target subscription.\n- A running ONTAP cluster reachable from the ANF delegated subnet.\n- All required environment variables populated in the active Postman environment (`tenant`, `subscriptionId`, `appId`, `clientSecret`, `accountName`, `resourceGroupName`, `poolName`, `ma.volumeName`, `ma.externalHostName`, `ma.serverName`, `ma.peerAddresses`, etc.).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "949385",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/949385-1c8cf438-bd48-45df-95d0-949dd2931beb?source=collection_link"
  },
