              ]
            },
            "description": "Requests an OAuth 2.0 bearer token from Azure Active Directory using the client credentials flow. The token is extracted from the response and stored in the `token` global variable, which is automatically used as a Bearer token in the Authorization header of all subsequent requests in this collection.\n\nTokens are valid for approximately 1 hour. Re-run this request if any subsequent call returns a `401 Unauthorized` error.\n\n**Required variables:** `authcloudurl`, `tenant`, `appId`, `clientSecret`"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Obtains an OAuth 2.0 bearer token from Azure Active Directory using client credentials (service principal). The token is stored as a global variable (`token`) and is automatically included as a Bearer token in the Authorization header of all subsequent ANF API requests.\n\n**Run this folder first** before executing any other folder in the collection. Tokens are valid for 1 hour; re-run this request if you receive `401 Unauthorized` responses.\n\n**Required variables:** `authcloudurl`, `tenant`, `appId`, `clientSecret`, `subscriptionId`"
    },
    {
