      "description": "Creates the ANF target volume and establishes the external replication relationship between the source ONTAP cluster and Azure NetApp Files. Run these steps in order to set up the migration pipeline.\n\n**Steps**\n\n1. **Create Target Volume** — Provisions the ANF volume that will receive replicated data from the source ONTAP volume. The volume is created in migration mode (`\"migrationVolume\": true`).\n2. **Check Volume Creation Progress** — Polls the Azure async operation URL to confirm the volume has been successfully provisioned before proceeding.\n3. **Issue Cluster Peer Request** — Initiates cluster peering between the source ONTAP cluster and ANF, returning the ONTAP peering command and a one-time passphrase.\n4. **Get Cluster Peering Command & Passphrase** — Polls the async operation to retrieve the ONTAP CLI command needed to complete cluster peering on the source side.\n5. **Authorize External Replication** — Authorizes the external replication relationship on the ANF volume, triggering the initial baseline data transfer from the source volume.\n6. **get vserver peering command** — Polls the async operation to retrieve the SVM (vserver) peering command required to complete the SVM peer relationship on the source ONTAP cluster.\n\n**Required variables:** `apicloudurl`, `subscriptionId`, `resourceGroupName`, `accountName`, `poolName`, `ma.volumeName`, `ma.externalHostName`, `ma.serverName`, `ma.peerAddresses`, `api-version`",
